    "hpi": [
      "68-year-old man with a history of chronic lung disease presents with shortness of breath. He reports feeling increasingly winded over the past several days, noting that activities he normally tolerate--such as walking from room to room--now require frequent pauses to catch his breath. He describes a persistent cough that has become more productive, though he is unsure if the sputum has changed in color. He endorses feeling warm at home with intermittent chills but states he has not measured his temperature. He denies chest pain, palpitations, or leg swelling. He does not use oxygen at baseline and states he usually gets better with inhalers, though he admits he has been using them more frequently than usual without much relief. EMS reports the patient was tachypneic and speaking in short phrases on scene. Prehospital ECG showed sinus tachycardia with left ventricular hypertrophy and no acute ischemic changes."
